From 253a20fc5d429e38e0b761977f2eff80c119a86c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 12:24:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] inline-3d(#625): reconcile macOS runtime-side weave onto
 browser#18/#22
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Rebase the mac overlay-path weave backend onto displayxr-browser main
(Windows browser 0.1.5 = patches 0043-0051: browser#18/#22 excludeElement
2D-overlay exclusion + DP-composited whole-window present).

- 17 mac-only files apply clean (weave_client_mac, weave_gpu_mac, BUILD.gn,
  chrome un-gates, shared_image widening, overlay_candidate + skia_renderer
  idle-ring / scroll-fix / multi-element — main never touches these).
- 4 of the 7 conflict files auto-merged (weave_provider.{cc,h},
  direct_renderer.h, display.cc — additive Win+Mac).
- 3 hand-merged: displayxr_weave_client.cc (IS_WIN/IS_MAC dispatcher);
  skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.{cc,h} (take main s #22 whole-window
  WeaveCompositedSurface, DROP the dead mac STEP-5 FinishPaint path,
  re-insert only the live overlay-path MaybeWeaveOverlaysMac hook).

Supersedes the browser-side whole-window stopgap (e0be91ca).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
